---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Biografía">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div
    class="min-h-screen bg-[url('../assets/biografia.jpeg')] bg-black/50 bg-blend-overlay bg-cover bg-center flex flex-col justify-end"
  >
    <h2 class="text-5xl text-white pl-20 font-semibold mb-10">Biografía</h2>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <div
        class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-blue-500"
      >
        <p class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Próxima Temporada 2025-2026
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          El tenor español ha sido seleccionado para formar parte del Roster de
          cantantes del Opernstudio de la Berlín Staatsoper Unter den Linden en
          la temporada 2025-2026.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p>
        In the 2025–2026 season, he will make his debut at the Gran Teatre del
        Liceu, singing the role of the “Maestro di Ballo” in Manon Lescaut,
        conducted by Josep Pons. He will also make his debut at the Teatro Pérez
        Galdós in Las Palmas de Gran Canaria with the role of “Pang” in
        Turandot, conducted by Sesto Quatrini.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the 2024/2025 season is part of the Roster of singers at the
        Opernstudio of the Opernhaus Zurich interpreting “Servo D'amelia” in
        Ballo in Maschera conducted by G.Noseda, “Maestro di Ballo” in Manon
        Lescaut conducted by M. Armiliato in Bary Koski's production, “Graf
        Albert” in Die Tote Stadt conducted by L.Viotti and will end his season
        as “Fourth Jew” conducted by S.Young.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2022 he is awarded with the first prize and audience award at the X
        Certamen de Habaneras para Solistas in Torrevieja. In the IV Concurso de
        canto Ciudad de Albacete he wins the José Ferrero prize for the best
        tenor and in the I Concurso de Canto Lírico de Tomelloso he receives the
        second prize. In 2023 he won the Victoria de los Ángeles prize at the VI
        Concurs Palet in Martorell and the third prize at the XI Concurso de
        Canto Lírico “Germans Plà” in Balaguer.
      </p>
      <p>
        He has debuted in roles such as “Alfredo” in Traviata, “Rinuccio” in
        Gianni Schicchi, “Ferrando” in Così Fan Tutte, “Don Basilio” and “Don
        Curzio” in Nozze di Figaro, “Belfiore” in Viaggio a Reims, “Don Ottavio”
        in Don Giovanni and “Prince Charmant” in Cendrillon in Palau de les Arts
        Reina Sofía.
      </p>
      <p>
        He has received masterclasses from masters such as Ramon Vargas, Hedwig
        Fassbender, Brigitte Fasbaender, Eytan Pessen, Isabel Rey, Ana Luisa
        Chova, Andrew Owens, Giovanni Sala, David Menendez, Charles Castronovo,
        George Petean, Adrian Kelly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
